4 HJR___ CONGRATULATING THE BISHOP STATE COMMUNITY COLLEGE
5 MEN'S BASKETBALL TEAM FOR WINNING THE 2026 ALABAMA COMMUNITY
6 COLLEGE CONFERENCE DIVISION I CHAMPIONSHIP.
7
8 WHEREAS, the Bishop State Community College Men's
9 Basketball Team, the Wildcats, captured the first Alabama
10 Community College Conference (ACCC) Division I Championship
11 in program history on March 14, 2026, by defeating Shelton
12 State Community College with a final score of 71–68; and
13 WHEREAS, with the historic victory, the Wildcats have
14 earned an automatic berth to the National Junior College
15 Athletic Association (NJCAA) Division I National Tournament
16 in Hutchinson, Kansas, representing the South District; and
17 WHEREAS, the Wildcats finished the conference
18 tournament with a resilient 17–15 record, overcoming
19 adversity and a young roster to secure their spot at the top
20 of the conference; and
21 WHEREAS, the victory marks the program's second
22 championship game appearance in the past three years and its
23 first ACCC title during that span, signaling the continued
24 growth of the Wildcats' basketball program; and
25 WHEREAS, the talented athletes on the Bishop State
26 Men's Basketball Team are Zion Mitchell, Kaymen Brown,
27 Vophcy Prophete, Tahsheim Gary, Jeremiah Sem, Jason
28 Noumbissi, Tramello Carter, Patrick Olajuwon, Jacob Feagin,
Page 1

Noumbissi, Tramello Carter, Patrick Olajuwon, Jacob Feagin,
HJR269 INTRODUCED
29 Maylon Martes, Nathadeus Fambro, and Keiman Franklin; and
30 WHEREAS, under the expert leadership and guidance of
31 Head Coach and Athletic Director Trent Eager, along with
32 Assistant Coaches Vincent Driscoll, Kirven Lang, and Mychal
33 Reddix, the Wildcats demonstrated exceptional skill,
34 perseverance, and teamwork throughout the 2025-2026 season;
35 and
36 WHEREAS, this landmark achievement has brought
37 immense pride and distinction to Bishop State Community
38 College, the City of Mobile, and the entire Alabama
39 Community College System; now therefore,
40 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
41 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That we commend and congratulate
42 the Bishop State Community College Men's Basketball Team
43 members and coaches for their remarkable achievement in
44 winning the 2026 ACCC Division I Championship, and we hereby
45 dedicate this resolution to them in utmost admiration, along
46 with best wishes for success in the national tournament.
